We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
provide a specific budget for the Solid Waste Programs and Activities particularly for the closure and rehabilitation of the dumpsite and implement the same;
allocate fund for establishment of sanitary landfill as stated in the SWMP of the Municipality;
avail of the fund set aside as Solid Waste Management Fund in the National Treasury pursuant to Section 46 of R.A. No. 9003;
require the MENRO or the assigned personnel to perform monitoring of projects and programs relative to Environmental Services to ensure implementation of the projects on time.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive instruct the Accountant to 

(a) require bonding of special disbursing officers; 

(b) limit the payment against cash advances to ₱15,000.00 and to transactions that are petty and are impractical to be paid in check; 
(c) scrutinize the liquidation and its supporting documents before recording in the books to avoid disbursements with incomplete documentation; 

(d) require the submission of lacking documents for the liquidation of cash advances amounting to ₱35,000.00; 

(e) discontinue granting of Cash advances to elected officials other than traveling expenses; 

(f) require the settlement or accounting of cash advances as soon as the purpose of the grant has been served; 


(g) require settlement of previous cash advance prior to granting of a new cash advance to officers and employees; and 

(h) send written notices/demand letters to concerned officials and employees with outstanding cash advances to enforce its settlement.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:  

a.	follow up and secure the approved copy of the Ten-Year Solid Waste Management Plan;

b.	provide a specific budget for the Solid Waste Programs and Activities particularly for the closure and rehabilitation of the dumpsite and establishment of sanitary landfill;

c.	avail of the fund set aside as Solid Waste Management Fund in the National Treasury pursuant to Section 46 of R.A. No. 9003;


d.	implement rehabilitation of the controlled dumpsite;

e.	allocate funds for the establishment of sanitary landfill pursuant to Section 16(h) of R.A. No. 9003;

f.	provide facility for composting of biodegradable wastes; and


g.	require the MENRO or the assigned personnel to perform monitoring of projects and programs relative to Environmental Services to ensure implementation of the projects on time.

